              fill="none" 
              stroke="currentColor" 
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            >
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
            </svg>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Getting Started: Video Marketing Best Practices for 2025</h2>
          </button>
        </div>
        
        <div id="getting-started-content" class="hidden ml-12">
          <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 mb-6">
            Starting your video marketing journey doesn't require a massive budget or professional equipment. Here's what Chicago businesses need to know to create effective video content that drives results.
          </p>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100 mb-4">Content That Works</h3>
          
          <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 mb-4">
            <strong>Short-form videos</strong> between 30 seconds to 2 minutes consistently deliver maximum engagement. These bite-sized pieces of content are perfect for social media platforms and hold viewers' attention in our fast-paced digital world.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 mb-4">
            <strong>Product demonstrations and tutorials</strong> showcase your offerings in action, helping potential customers understand value and functionality. These videos answer common questions and reduce purchase hesitation.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 mb-4">
            <strong>Customer testimonials and success stories</strong> provide social proof that builds trust and credibility. Real customers sharing authentic experiences carry more weight than traditional advertising claims.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 mb-6">
            <strong>Behind-the-scenes content</strong> humanizes your brand and builds emotional connections. Show your team, your process, or your company culture to create authentic relationships with your audience.
          </p>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100 mb-4">Platform Strategy</h3>
          
          <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 mb-4">
            <strong>Facebook and Instagram</strong> offer the broadest reach for most businesses. These platforms excel at community building and brand awareness, with sophisticated targeting options for local Chicago businesses.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 mb-4">
            <strong>LinkedIn</strong> is essential for B2B connections and professional services. The platform's business-focused audience makes it ideal for thought leadership content and industry expertise demonstrations.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 mb-4">
            <strong>YouTube</strong> serves as the go-to platform for long-form educational content. It functions as both a social platform and search engine, making it valuable for SEO and establishing expertise.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 mb-6">
            <strong>Your website</strong> should host key videos for SEO benefits and complete control over the viewing experience. Embedded videos increase time on site and improve search rankings.
          </p>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100 mb-4">Production Tips</h3>
          
          <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 mb-4">
            <strong>Focus on good lighting and clear audio.</strong> Poor audio quality will lose viewers faster than poor video quality. Natural lighting from windows often works better than expensive equipment for beginners.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 mb-4">
            <strong>Keep videos mobile-friendly</strong> by using vertical or square formats. Over 75% of video consumption happens on mobile devices, so optimize for small screens from the start.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 mb-4">
            <strong>Include captions for accessibility</strong> and silent viewing. Many users watch videos without sound, especially on social media, making captions essential for engagement.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 mb-6">
            <strong>Start with a hook in the first 3 seconds</strong> and end with a clear call-to-action. Capture attention immediately and guide viewers toward your desired next step.
          </p>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100 mb-4">Budget Allocation</h3>
          
          <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 mb-4">
            <strong>Start with 20-30% of your digital marketing budget</strong> allocated to video content. This allows for experimentation while maintaining other marketing channels during the transition.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 mb-4">
            <strong>Invest in basic equipment and editing software</strong> before hiring agencies. A good smartphone, tripod, and simple editing app can produce professional-looking content for most small businesses.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 mb-4">
            <strong>Consider outsourcing complex projects</strong> while handling simple content in-house. This hybrid approach maximizes budget efficiency and maintains consistent content flow.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400">
            <strong>Track ROI and adjust spending accordingly.</strong> Use analytics to identify which video types and platforms deliver the best results, then reinvest profits into expanding successful video efforts.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
